<T>__{dissolve to:}
<L>__{exterior. eighth street night}
<A>__{we look down on eighth street in greenwich village. it is eight thirty at night. it is a fairly active and well lit street, bright with neons and movie marquees and lit up shops. our five carousers are marching down the sidewalk, that is four of them are on the sidewalk. walter can't quite decide whether he wants to walk on the sidewalk or in the street. he keeps hopping in and out between the parked cars, running to catch up when he falls behind. they are all feeling pretty good. arnold is singing in a wavering baritone:}
